In a #pot{} for the couscous, dilute the @beef stock{1%sachet} in 200ml @water{200%ml} (500ml for 4p). Bring to the boil. When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{100%g} and pop a #lid{} on the pot. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks. Quarter the @lime{1}(quartered). Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Trim half the @cucumber{½}(trimmed and quartered lengthways, then chopped widthways) (double for 4p), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Thinly slice the @Irish beef rump{250%g}. When pan is hot, add the beef slices and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Move the beef slices to one side of the pan and add the onion to the empty side.

Fry the onion, stirring occasionally, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir the beef and onion together for another ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet} along with 50ml water (double for 4p). Allow to warm through for ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if required.

Meanwhile, fluff up the couscous with a fork. Stir through the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}, chopped cucumber and tomato. Season to taste with salt, pepper and lime juice.

Divide the couscous between #bowls{}. Top with beef slices and teriyaki sauce. Sprinkle over the sliced scallion. Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside.